data.title: Facts, Childhood, Family Life & Achievements
data.meta_description: A behind-the-scene look at the life of will.i.am.
data.text:
will.i.am is a founding member of the Black Eyed Peas and serves as the group's rapper and producer.

will.i.am served as a coach on the UK version of "The Voice" from 2012 to 2016.

will.i.am founded the tech company i.am+ which focuses on consumer electronics and wearable technology.

will.i.am collaborated with Britney Spears on the hit song "Scream & Shout" in 2012.

will.i.am voiced the character of Moto Moto in the animated film "Madagascar: Escape 2 Africa".

will.i.am is a tech enthusiast and has invested in several technology startups, showing his passion for innovation beyond music.

He is a strong advocate for education and has worked on various initiatives to support STEM education for underprivileged youth.

will.i.am has a keen interest in fashion and has launched his own clothing line, showcasing his creativity in different artistic fields.

He is a talented voice actor and has lent his voice to characters in popular animated films, demonstrating his versatility as an artist.
